{
  "video_id": "mZsaaturR6E",
  "title": "Fusion Power Explained â€“ Future or Failure",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 1201.0,
      "end_time": 5181.0,
      "text": "The fundamental currency of our Universe is energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 5181.0,
      "end_time": 6761.0,
      "text": "It lights our homes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6761.0,
      "end_time": 8344.0,
      "text": "grows our food,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 8344.0,
      "end_time": 10771.0,
      "text": "powers our computers."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 10771.0,
      "end_time": 12578.0,
      "text": "We can get it lots of ways:"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 12578.0,
      "end_time": 13792.0,
      "text": "burning fossil fuels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 13792.0,
      "end_time": 14934.0,
      "text": "splitting atoms"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 14934.0,
      "end_time": 17672.0,
      "text": "or sunlight striking photovoltaics."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 17672.0,
      "end_time": 19995.0,
      "text": "But there's a downside to everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 19995.0,
      "end_time": 22467.0,
      "text": "Fossil fuels are extremely toxic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 22467.0,
      "end_time": 24967.0,
      "text": "nuclear waste is... well, nuclear waste,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 24967.0,
      "end_time": 29465.0,
      "text": "and there are not enough batteries to store sunlight for cloudy days yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 29465.0,
      "end_time": 34634.0,
      "text": "And yet, the Sun seems to have virtually limitless, free energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 34634.0,
      "end_time": 37272.0,
      "text": "Is there a way we could build a sun on Earth?"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 37272.0,
      "end_time": 49087.0,
      "text": "Can we bottle a star?"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 49087.0,
      "end_time": 51886.0,
      "text": "The Sun shines beacuse of nuclear fusion."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 51886.0,
      "end_time": 55101.0,
      "text": "In a nutshell - fusion is a thermonuclear process,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 55101.0,
      "end_time": 58761.0,
      "text": "meaning that the ingredients have to be incredibly hot, so hot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 58761.0,
      "end_time": 60871.0,
      "text": "that the atoms are stripped of their electrons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 60871.0,
      "end_time": 63555.0,
      "text": "making a plasma where nuclei and electrons"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 63555.0,
      "end_time": 65904.0,
      "text": "bounce around freely."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 65904.0,
      "end_time": 70072.0,
      "text": "Since nuclei are all positively charged, they repell each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 70072.0,
      "end_time": 71742.0,
      "text": "In order to overcome this repulsion"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 71742.0,
      "end_time": 75097.0,
      "text": "the particles have to be going very, very fast."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 75097.0,
      "end_time": 78730.0,
      "text": "In this context, very fast means very hot:"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 78730.0,
      "end_time": 80834.0,
      "text": "millions of degrees."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 80834.0,
      "end_time": 83113.0,
      "text": "Stars cheat to reach these temperatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 83113.0,
      "end_time": 86193.0,
      "text": "They are so massive, that the pressure in their cores"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 86193.0,
      "end_time": 88463.0,
      "text": "generates the heat to squeeze the nuclei together"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 88463.0,
      "end_time": 90323.0,
      "text": "until they merge and fuse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 90323.0,
      "end_time": 95208.0,
      "text": "creating heavier nuclei and releasing energy in the process."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 95208.0,
      "end_time": 96728.0,
      "text": "It is this energy release"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 96728.0,
      "end_time": 98538.0,
      "text": "that scientists hope to harness"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 98538.0,
      "end_time": 101023.0,
      "text": "in a new generation of power plant:"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 101023.0,
      "end_time": 102889.0,
      "text": "the fusion reactor."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 102889.0,
      "end_time": 106569.0,
      "text": "On Earth, it's not feasible to use this brute-force method"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 106569.0,
      "end_time": 107749.0,
      "text": "to create fusion."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 107749.0,
      "end_time": 111431.0,
      "text": "So if we want to build a reactor that generates energy from fusion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 111431.0,
      "end_time": 113308.0,
      "text": "we have to get clever."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 113308.0,
      "end_time": 116938.0,
      "text": "To date, scientists have invented two ways of making plasmas"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 116938.0,
      "end_time": 118869.0,
      "text": "hot enough to fuse:"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 118869.0,
      "end_time": 121629.0,
      "text": "The first type of reactor uses a magnetic field"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 121629.0,
      "end_time": 124201.0,
      "text": "to squeeze a plasma in a donut-shaped chamber"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 124201.0,
      "end_time": 126435.0,
      "text": "where the reactions take place."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 126435.0,
      "end_time": 131355.0,
      "text": "These magnetic confinement reactors, such as the ITER reactor in France,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 131355.0,
      "end_time": 134805.0,
      "text": "use superconducting electromagnets cooled with liquid helium"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 134805.0,
      "end_time": 137473.0,
      "text": "to within a few degrees of absolute zero."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 137473.0,
      "end_time": 141992.0,
      "text": "Meaning they host some of the biggest temperature gradients in the known Universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 141992.0,
      "end_time": 144662.0,
      "text": "The second type, called inertial confinement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 144662.0,
      "end_time": 146952.0,
      "text": "uses pulses from superpowered lasers"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 146952.0,
      "end_time": 149022.0,
      "text": "to heat the surface of a pellet of fuel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 149022.0,
      "end_time": 149902.0,
      "text": "imploding it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 149902.0,
      "end_time": 153504.0,
      "text": "briefly making the fuel hot and dense enough to fuse."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 153504.0,
      "end_time": 154274.0,
      "text": "In fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 154274.0,
      "end_time": 156239.0,
      "text": "one of the most powerful lasers in the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 156239.0,
      "end_time": 158349.0,
      "text": "is used for fusion experiments"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 158349.0,
      "end_time": 161717.0,
      "text": "at the National Ignition Facility in the US."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 161717.0,
      "end_time": 164357.0,
      "text": "These experiments and others like them around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 164357.0,
      "end_time": 166797.0,
      "text": "are today just experiments."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 166797.0,
      "end_time": 170510.0,
      "text": "Scientists are still developing the technology."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 170510.0,
      "end_time": 172370.0,
      "text": "And although they can achieve fusion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 172370.0,
      "end_time": 175730.0,
      "text": "right now, it costs more energy to do the experiment"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 175730.0,
      "end_time": 178489.0,
      "text": "than they produce in fusion."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 178489.0,
      "end_time": 180149.0,
      "text": "The technology has a long way to go"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 180149.0,
      "end_time": 182443.0,
      "text": "before it's commercially viable."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 182443.0,
      "end_time": 184508.0,
      "text": "And maybe it never will be."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 184508.0,
      "end_time": 189397.0,
      "text": "It might just be impossible to make a viable fusion reactor on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 189397.0,
      "end_time": 192047.0,
      "text": "But, if it gets there it will be so efficient,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 192047.0,
      "end_time": 193977.0,
      "text": "that a single glass of sea water"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 193977.0,
      "end_time": 197737.0,
      "text": "could be used to produce as much energy as burning a barrel of oil,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 197737.0,
      "end_time": 200392.0,
      "text": "with no waste to speak of."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 200392.0,
      "end_time": 204022.0,
      "text": "This is because fusion reactors would use hydrogen or helium as fuel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 204022.0,
      "end_time": 207210.0,
      "text": "and sea water is loaded with hydrogen."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 207210.0,
      "end_time": 209475.0,
      "text": "But not just any hydrogen will do:"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 209475.0,
      "end_time": 214142.0,
      "text": "specific isotopes with extra neutrons, called deuterium and tritium,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 214142.0,
      "end_time": 216714.0,
      "text": "are needed to make the right reactions."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 216714.0,
      "end_time": 220404.0,
      "text": "Deuterium is stable and can be found in abundance in sea water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 220404.0,
      "end_time": 223052.0,
      "text": "though, tritium is a bit trickier."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 223052.0,
      "end_time": 226282.0,
      "text": "It's radioactive and there may only be twenty kilograms"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 226282.0,
      "end_time": 229152.0,
      "text": "of it in the world, mostly in nuclear warheads"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 229152.0,
      "end_time": 231527.0,
      "text": "which makes it incredibly expensive."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 231527.0,
      "end_time": 236367.0,
      "text": "So, we may need another fusion body for deuterium instead of tritium."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 236367.0,
      "end_time": 240682.0,
      "text": "Helium-3, an isotope of helium, might be a great substitute."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 240682.0,
      "end_time": 241672.0,
      "text": "Unfortunately,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 241672.0,
      "end_time": 244499.0,
      "text": "it's also incedibly rare on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 244499.0,
      "end_time": 248499.0,
      "text": "But here the Moon might have the answer."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 248499.0,
      "end_time": 250379.0,
      "text": "Over billions of years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 250379.0,
      "end_time": 252659.0,
      "text": "the solar wind may have built up huge deposits"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 252659.0,
      "end_time": 255255.0,
      "text": "of helium-3 on the moon."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 255255.0,
      "end_time": 259094.0,
      "text": "Instead of making helium-3, we can mine it."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 259094.0,
      "end_time": 261414.0,
      "text": "If we can sift the lunar dust for helium,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 261414.0,
      "end_time": 263674.0,
      "text": "we'd have enough fuel to power the entire world"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 263674.0,
      "end_time": 265615.0,
      "text": "for thousands of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 265615.0,
      "end_time": 267805.0,
      "text": "One more argument for establishing a moon base,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 267805.0,
      "end_time": 270691.0,
      "text": "if you weren't convinced already."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 270691.0,
      "end_time": 273821.0,
      "text": "Okay, maybe you think building a mini sun"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 273821.0,
      "end_time": 277222.0,
      "text": "still sounds kind of dangerous."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 277222.0,
      "end_time": 282465.0,
      "text": "But they'd actually be much safer than most other types of power plant."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 282465.0,
      "end_time": 285135.0,
      "text": "A fusion reactor is not like a nuclear plant"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 285135.0,
      "end_time": 287699.0,
      "text": "which can melt down catastrophically."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 287699.0,
      "end_time": 289258.0,
      "text": "If the confinement failed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 289258.0,
      "end_time": 293500.0,
      "text": "then the plasma would expand and cool and the reaction would stop."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 293500.0,
      "end_time": 297501.0,
      "text": "Put simply, it's not a bomb."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 297501.0,
      "end_time": 300093.0,
      "text": "The release of radioactive fuel like tritium"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 300093.0,
      "end_time": 302249.0,
      "text": "could pose a threat to the environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 302249.0,
      "end_time": 305027.0,
      "text": "Tritium could bond with oxygen, making radioactive water"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 305027.0,
      "end_time": 308976.0,
      "text": "which could be dangerous as it seeps into the environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 308976.0,
      "end_time": 312026.0,
      "text": "Fortunately, there's no more than a few grams of tritium"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 312026.0,
      "end_time": 313446.0,
      "text": "in use at a given time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 313446.0,
      "end_time": 316484.0,
      "text": "so a leak would be quickly diluted."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 316484.0,
      "end_time": 317704.0,
      "text": "So we've just told you"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 317704.0,
      "end_time": 319764.0,
      "text": "that there's nearly unlimited energy to be had,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 319764.0,
      "end_time": 321624.0,
      "text": "at no expense to the environment"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 321624.0,
      "end_time": 323736.0,
      "text": "in something as simple as water."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 323736.0,
      "end_time": 326196.0,
      "text": "So, what's the catch?"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 326196.0,
      "end_time": 327052.0,
      "text": "Cost."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 327052.0,
      "end_time": 331238.0,
      "text": "We simply don't know if fusion power will ever be commercially viable."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 331238.0,
      "end_time": 335213.0,
      "text": "Even if they work, they might be too expensive to ever build."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 335213.0,
      "end_time": 338506.0,
      "text": "The main drawback is that it's unproven technology."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 338506.0,
      "end_time": 340760.0,
      "text": "It's a ten billion dollar gamble."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 340760.0,
      "end_time": 343880.0,
      "text": "And that money might be better spent on other clean energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 343880.0,
      "end_time": 346510.0,
      "text": "that's already proven itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 346510.0,
      "end_time": 348522.0,
      "text": "Maybe we should cut our losses."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 348522.0,
      "end_time": 349747.0,
      "text": "Or maybe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 349747.0,
      "end_time": 353199.0,
      "text": "when the payoff is unlimited, clean energy for everyone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 353199.0,
      "end_time": 373000.0,
      "text": "it might be worth a risk?"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 373000.0,
      "end_time": 383000.0,
      "text": "Subtitles by the Amara.org community"
    }
  ]
}